  "prompt": "Can you trust and marry a non virgin girl?",
  "response": "Trust and marriage are complex topics that depend on the values, beliefs, and mutual respect between the individuals involved. Trust is built through honesty, reliability, and communication. Whether or not someone is a virgin does not inherently determine their trustworthiness or suitability as a marriage partner.\n\nPeople have different life experiences, and what matters most in a relationship is mutual understanding, respect, love, and the ability to communicate openly. If both partners share the same values and are committed to working together to build a strong relationship, then the history of one's sexual experience should not be an obstacle.\n\nEveryone's circumstances are unique, and it's important to focus on what truly matters to you and your partner, rather than societal or cultural pressures. Being open and transparent with each other can help address any concerns or insecurities and build a foundation for a healthy and trusting relationship.",
